snippet: Reflecting a global problem, a cluster of moon jellyfish clogged the cooling water intake pipes of the world’s largest boiling-water nuclear reactor, in southeastern Sweden, forcing its shutdown.
abstract: Huge cluster of moon jellyfish clog cooling water intake pipes at Oskarshamn nuclear power plant in Sweden, forcing the complex’s 1,400-megawatt Unit 3 to shut down; episode reflects continuing global problem.
lead_paragraph: Reflecting a global problem, a cluster of moon jellyfish clogged the cooling water intake pipes of the world’s largest boiling-water nuclear reactor, in southeastern Sweden, forcing its shutdown.
